All 3 sides used this rifle and others smuggled in to sow terror by indiscriminately fire to decimate their respective enemies. The Yugoslavs chambered this rifle in 8mm because their Nazi stocks of captured weapons after WWII were in this caliber and their factories were already tooled up for this excellent, flat shooting, high velocity round. Also important was the fact that the dictators: Stalin and Tito were none too fond of one another to the point that Yugoslavia, who had lost 1.5 million men in the war weren't about to be bullied by the Russians. Tito also refused to become a member of the Warsaw Pact which partially meant they could, to a point, use their own designs in firearm development as they were non-aligned. This rifle uses a modified Kalashnikov action and is loosely patterned after the Dragunov and was produced in the Zastava factory which is still carved out of a mountainside only accessed by steel blast doors using machinery that was manufactured by the same factory that manufactured what is considered to be one of the world's best AK's and other small arms. Not many were brought over and all the pre ban rifles were confiscated by the ATF since they were later considered machine guns as the sear was considered to be easily manipulated to fire in the automatic mode. I like this rifle better than the Tiger and it is light years ahead of the unfortunate Romanians whose AK's are considered by some to be the worst made small arms of the world. This rifle has not fallen victim to the few rifles of thiis model I have seen in shops abd shows: some uunscrupulous dealers have removed the range finding Zrak scope with Chinese cheapy scopes and selling the Zrak scopes to maximize their profit. Comes with two ten round magazine that eerily resembles the German G or K-43 magazines of their time. Thirty round after market magazines are available as an accessory. Looks like they are welded Solothurn mags. Anyway, this rifle has a forged receiver to enhance accuracy and will be among top collectibles in years to come. No trades or offers. A confortable rifle to shoot and quite accurate with the correct ammunition. $1500
